1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,520
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,520
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,520 --> 00:00:07,880
My name is Catherine.
我是Catherine。

4
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:13,800
And today we've got a very interesting lesson for you all about building your vocabulary.
今天我们为大家准备了一节非常有趣的课，关于如何扩充词汇量。

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:16,880
So we're trying to describe personalities.
我们要尝试描述性格。

6
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:19,120
You're going to learn tons of new words.
你会学到很多新词。

7
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:20,120
Exactly.
没错。

8
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:22,840
And as you said, we're going to describe people's personalities.
就像你说的，我们要描述人的性格。

9
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:24,960
So not their physical attributes.
而不是他们的外貌特征。

10
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:29,920
We're going to concentrate on how they are personality wise and stuff like that.
我们会专注于他们的性格特点之类的。

11
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:30,920
Their character.
他们的品性。

12
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:31,920
That's right.
对。

13
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:35,600
So let's take a listen to today's dialogue for the first time and we'll be back in a
那我们先听一遍今天的对话，

14
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:40,320
moment to talk about some of these great words.
稍后再回来讨论这些精彩的词汇。

15
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:46,080
Okay, class, settle down.
好了，同学们，安静下来。

16
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:49,480
I have the results of your individual personality tests.
我拿到了你们个人性格测试的结果。

17
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:53,560
I'm going to hand them out and if you'd like, you can read them out loud to the rest of
我会发下去，如果你们愿意，可以大声读给全班同学听。

18
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,560
the class.


19
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,560
I'll read mine.
我来读我的。

20
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:57,080
Okay, go ahead.
好的，请吧。

21
00:00:57,080 --> 00:01:00,840
It says here that I am adventurous, outgoing and easygoing.
上面说我爱冒险、外向、随和。

22
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:04,880
It says that I'm a little superstitious and occasionally naive.
还说我有那么一点迷信，偶尔天真。

23
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:05,880
That's not true.
那不是真的。

24
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:09,280
Well, the test isn't 100% accurate.
嗯，这个测试不是百分之百准确。

25
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:10,720
Is that all it says?
就这些吗？

26
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,720
No.
不。

27
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:16,240
It also says that I'm open minded with great ambition, but that I can also be reckless
还说我有开放的心态、雄心勃勃，但也可能鲁莽

28
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,840
and clumsy.
和笨手笨脚。

29
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,160
This is stupid.
这太蠢了。

30
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,200
Okay.
好吧。

31
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:22,120
Anyone else want to read theirs?
还有其他人想读自己的吗？

32
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:23,120
I'll go.
我来。

33
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,840
It says that I'm an extroverted, well balanced person.
上面说我是一个外向、平衡的人。

34
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,920
It says I am generous, outspoken and very diligent.
说我慷慨、直言不讳、非常勤奋。

35
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,300
This is so true.
这太准了。

36
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:34,040
It also says that I am a magnanimous, eloquent and daring.
还说我宽宏大量、口才好、勇敢。

37
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:36,040
This is totally me.
这完全就是我。

38
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,120
Whatever.
随便吧。

39
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:40,080
These tests are baloney.
这些测试都是胡扯。

40
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:44,680
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

41
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:49,140
So we're going to divide this up into language takeaway parts one and two.
我们会把这部分分成语言要点第一和第二部分。

42
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:56,040
So let's start with five key words now on language takeaway.
现在先从语言要点的五个关键词开始。

43
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:58,320
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

44
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:03,200
The first adjective that came up was adventurous and outgoing.
第一个出现的形容词是爱冒险和外向。

45
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,340
Outgoing, that's a good one.
外向，这个词不错。

46
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:06,400
Outgoing is a great one.
外向是个好词。

47
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,000
So think of the word out.
想想“out”这个词。

48
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,360
That means moving out, going out.
意思是向外、出去。

49
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:17,820
Outgoing means someone is very comfortable talking to strangers or talking to people
外向指的是一个人很擅长和陌生人或不熟悉的人交谈。

50
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,960
that they don't know very well.


51
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,560
For example, my brother is very outgoing.
比如，我哥哥非常外向。

52
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,600
He loves meeting new people.
他喜欢认识新朋友。

53
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:27,640
He loves starting conversations with strangers.
他喜欢和陌生人搭话。

54
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,480
So the opposite would be shy.
所以反义词是害羞。

55
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:30,480
That's the opposite.
那就是反义词。

56
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,280
Okay, so outgoing.
好的，所以是外向。

57
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:37,520
And then it also described this person as being a little superstitious.
然后它还描述这个人有点迷信。

58
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:45,320
Okay, superstitious is very interesting because it's hard to describe since everyone's superstitions
好的，迷信这个词很有意思，因为很难描述，每个人的迷信都不一样。

59
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,360
are different.


60
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:49,000
In many cultures, there are different superstitions.
在很多文化中，有不同的迷信。

61
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:54,880
So for example, in America, we say that walking under a ladder is bad luck.
比如，在美国，我们说从梯子下走过会带来坏运气。

62
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:58,200
Or opening an umbrella inside is bad luck.
或者在室内打开雨伞会带来坏运气。

63
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:03,920
So if you believe that your actions will bring you bad luck, you're probably superstitious.
所以如果你相信你的行为会带来坏运气，那你可能就迷信。

64
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,200
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

65
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:09,840
So if you are superstitious, you believe in superstitions.
所以如果你迷信，你就相信迷信。

66
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,840
That's right.
没错。

67
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,840
So Marco, are you superstitious?
那么Marco，你迷信吗？

68
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,200
Do you think that black cats bring bad luck?
你觉得黑猫会带来坏运气吗？

69
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,200
No, not at all.
不，一点也不。

70
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,200
No.
不。

71
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,200
That's very interesting.
那很有意思。

72
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,200
All right.
好的。

73
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:23,120
And this is also an interesting word, a way to describe people who are very believing,
这也是一个有趣的词，用来描述非常轻信的人，

74
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,640
a person that is naive.
天真的人。

75
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,480
Okay, you said this already.
好的，你刚才说过了。

76
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:33,160
Naive means that someone generally believes most things that you tell them.
天真指的是一个人通常相信你告诉他的大部分事情。

77
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:38,560
So if I told you, Marco, hey, did you know that it's supposed to rain frogs tomorrow?
所以如果我告诉你，Marco，嘿，你知道吗，明天要下青蛙雨？

78
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,560
No way.
不会吧。

79
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,560
Really?
真的吗？

80
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,560
Yeah, really.
是的，真的。

81
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,020
If Marco believes me, he's naive.
如果马可相信我，那他就太天真了。

82
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:49,000
That means that probably it's not going to rain frogs tomorrow, but he believes everything
这意味着明天可能不会下青蛙雨，但他相信我说的

83
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
I say.
每一句话。

84
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,800
So he's a little bit naive or inexperienced.
所以他有点天真或缺乏经验。

85
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:56,120
So naive is not really a bad way of describing a person, is it?
所以“天真”并不是一个描述人的坏词，对吧？

86
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,560
No, but it can be.
不，但它可以是。

87
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,980
So you want to be careful.
所以你要小心。

88
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:02,600
Some people, if you say that they're being naive, it's offensive.
有些人，如果你说他们天真，那会冒犯到他们。

89
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:05,880
So you have to be careful when you say this.
所以你说这个词时要小心。

90
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:06,880
Okay.
好的。

91
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:12,080
Moving on, we also had an interesting adjective that described another person, and it was
继续，我们还有一个有趣的形容词，用来描述另一个人，那就是

92
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,080
to be reckless.
鲁莽。

93
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,880
I can also be reckless.
我也可以很鲁莽。

94
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:15,880
Reckless.
鲁莽。

95
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,880
Okay.
好的。

96
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:21,760
So someone who is reckless often does things without thinking, sometimes things that are
所以一个鲁莽的人经常做事不经思考，有时会做

97
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,760
dangerous.
危险的事。

98
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:28,680
For example, Marco, I think that driving a car without wearing your seatbelt is very
例如，马可，我觉得开车不系安全带是非常

99
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,680
reckless.
鲁莽的。

100
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,680
Okay.
好的。

101
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,480
That means that you're not thinking about safety.
这意味着你没有考虑安全。

102
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,480
Right.
对。

103
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:39,520
So a person that is reckless is a kind of a synonym of being a little bit dangerous to
所以一个鲁莽的人，某种程度上是那种待在一起有点

104
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,520
be around.
危险的人。

105
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,520
That's right.
没错。

106
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:45,960
So someone who does things without thinking about their consequences, their results.
所以就是做事不考虑后果、不考虑结果的人。

107
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,960
Okay.
好的。

108
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:51,320
And also along with reckless, the test said that this person was clumsy.
除了鲁莽，测试还说这个人很笨拙。

109
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,000
Oh, I love this word.
哦，我喜欢这个词。

110
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,560
There was a very famous commercial when I was growing up in America on the television.
我小时候在美国长大时，电视上有一个很有名的广告。

111
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:03,520
It was all about young students at high school who are clumsy, and so they should buy this
讲的是高中里笨拙的学生，所以他们应该买这种

112
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:10,080
special folder for their schoolwork to help them because they're so clumsy.
特殊的文件夹来帮助学习，因为他们太笨拙了。

113
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,160
And they're dropping their papers and their books.
他们总是掉纸和书。

114
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,160
Exactly.
没错。

115
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:18,920
So someone who is clumsy often falls down or hits their head or trips or drops their
所以一个笨拙的人经常摔倒、撞到头、绊倒或掉

116
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,600
things.
东西。

117
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:25,400
If I drop something on the floor and break it, my mother might say, you're so clumsy.
如果我把东西掉在地上摔碎了，我妈妈可能会说，你真笨拙。

118
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,400
Clumsy fingers.
笨手笨脚。

119
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,400
You should be more careful.
你应该更小心点。

120
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,400
Yeah.
是啊。

121
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:31,680
So clumsy, is this insulting if you say, oh, you're so clumsy?
所以“笨拙”这个词，如果你说“哦，你真笨拙”，这算冒犯吗？

122
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,440
No, it's not so bad.
不，没那么严重。

123
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:37,420
There are worse things to say.
还有更糟的话可以说。

124
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:40,280
But if someone often drops things, you can call them clumsy.
但如果有人经常掉东西，你可以说他们笨拙。

125
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:44,040
Or you can also say, you're such a butterfingers.
或者你也可以说，你真是个黄油手。

126
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,040
Butterfingers.
黄油手。

127
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,960
That means that your fingers are like butter.
意思是你的手指像黄油一样。

128
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:47,960
They're very slippery.
很滑。

129
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,200
You drop everything.
什么都拿不住。

130
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,200
Okay.
好的。

131
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:54,480
So clumsy and reckless, they are negative adjectives, right?
所以笨拙和鲁莽，都是负面形容词，对吧？

132
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,680
They're saying that you do things wrong.
它们是在说你做错了事。

133
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,880
So it's not really a good thing to be reckless or clumsy.
所以鲁莽或笨拙并不是好事。

134
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,240
No, it's not really a good thing.
不，确实不是好事。

135
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,440
These are not positive characteristics.
这些不是积极的性格特征。

136
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,880
Okay, good.
好的，明白了。

137
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:09,600
So we took a look at those five, which are very good about one of the people that took
所以我们看了这五个词，它们很好地描述了参加测试的一个人。

138
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,600
the test.
测试。

139
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:19,240
Let's move on now to more language and more adjectives on Language Takeaway part two.
现在让我们继续，在“语言摘录”第二部分中学习更多语言和形容词。

140
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,720
Language Takeaway.
语言摘录。

141
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:26,880
Alright, so in this part, we're going to take a look at positive attributes about a person,
好的，在这一部分，我们要看看一个人的积极特质，

142
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,880
right?
对吧？

143
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,320
They're all good things about someone.
都是关于一个人的好品质。

144
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,320
That's right.
没错。

145
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,520
And this first one is very good.
第一个词非常好。

146
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,520
Extroverted, extroverted.
外向的，外向的。

147
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,320
A person that's extroverted.
一个外向的人。

148
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:39,120
So a synonym of this word is outgoing.
所以这个词的同义词是“开朗的”。

149
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,560
Okay, so it's pretty much the same thing.
好的，所以基本上是一回事。

150
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:45,320
That's right, because extra means going out, out.
没错，因为“extra”意思是向外、出去。

151
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:51,360
So in this case, someone who is extroverted often meets new people, goes out and does
所以在这种情况下，一个外向的人经常结识新朋友，出去做

152
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:56,480
social things, goes to the movies, goes out with friends, meets strangers, talks to strangers.
社交活动，比如看电影、和朋友出去玩、见陌生人、和陌生人聊天。

153
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,520
Again, it's like being outgoing.
就像开朗一样。

154
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,240
Someone who's comfortable with new people.
一个和新人相处很自在的人。

155
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,160
And what about the opposite?
那反义词呢？

156
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,440
So we said that shy is the opposite of outgoing.
我们说害羞是开朗的反义词。

157
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:08,920
What would be the opposite for extroverted?
那外向的反义词是什么？

158
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:11,720
Extroverted's opposite is introverted.
外向的反义词是内向。

159
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:14,200
Intro means in, not out.
“Intro”意思是向内，不是向外。

160
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:18,480
So that means someone who's very shy, who is uncomfortable with new people.
所以那意味着一个非常害羞、和新人相处不自在的人。

161
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,480
Okay.
好的。

162
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:25,320
And well, apart from being extroverted, the test also said that this person is very diligent.
嗯，除了外向之外，测试还显示这个人非常勤奋。

163
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,200
Ooh, diligent is a great word.
哦，勤奋是个好词。

164
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:31,240
This is a word you want to hear from your teachers and your bosses.
这是你想从老师和老板那里听到的词。

165
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,280
Okay, if someone says, Marco, you're very diligent at work.
好的，如果有人对你说，马可，你在工作中非常勤奋。

166
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,280
What does that mean?
那是什么意思？

167
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,800
It means you're very careful.
意思是你非常细心。

168
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:40,480
You always do things very thoroughly.
你总是把事情做得非常彻底。

169
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,020
And also quickly, right?
而且还要快，对吧？

170
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:45,080
When you tell them to do something, they do it immediately.
当你让他们做某事时，他们会立刻去做。

171
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:46,080
That's right.
没错。

172
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:50,600
So a diligent worker always does a good job and does it in a timely manner.
所以一个勤奋的工人总是把工作做好，并且及时完成。

173
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,600
Okay.
好的。

174
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:54,280
And moving on to our third adjective.
接下来是我们的第三个形容词。

175
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,880
This one is kind of strange.
这个有点奇怪。

176
00:07:55,880 --> 00:08:00,520
It kind of sounds like monogamy, but it's magnanimous.
听起来有点像“一夫一妻制”，但它是“宽宏大量的”。

177
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,520
Magnanimous.
宽宏大量的。

178
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,520
All right.
好的。

179
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,520
Magnanimous.
宽宏大量的。

180
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,800
This is a great word.
这是个好词。

181
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:12,400
We hear this a lot in the newspaper or on TV about usually famous people.
我们经常在报纸或电视上听到这个词，通常用来形容名人。

182
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:16,780
He did something very magnanimous or it was a magnanimous gesture.
他做了一件非常宽宏大量的事，或者那是一个宽宏大量的姿态。

183
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:21,960
This describes a person who does things for the benefit of other people.
这个词描述的是一个为他人利益着想的人。

184
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:27,520
Who is thinking about the well-being and the health and the lives of others.
一个关心他人福祉、健康和生活的人。

185
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:31,680
So it would be a person that likes to share or a person that's not selfish.
所以，这是一个乐于分享的人，或者是一个不自私的人。

186
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,680
Right.
没错。

187
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:38,480
So if you donate half of your salary this month to victims of an earthquake, I would
所以，如果你这个月把一半的工资捐给地震灾民，我会

188
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,920
say, Marco, that's so magnanimous of you.
说，Marco，你真是太宽宏大量了。

189
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,480
You're so magnanimous.
你太宽宏大量了。

190
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,480
Okay.
好的。

191
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,480
Awesome.
太棒了。

192
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:50,720
And apart from being magnanimous, if a person is eloquent, I guess that's also a positive
除了宽宏大量之外，如果一个人能言善辩，我想那也是一个积极的

193
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,720
attribute.
特质。

194
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,720
Yeah.
是的。

195
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,360
This is another really good one.
这也是一个非常好的词。

196
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:58,160
Someone who is eloquent is a very good speaker.
能言善辩的人是一个很会说话的人。

197
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:03,080
This means that when they talk, they sound very, very good.
这意味着他们说话时，听起来非常非常好。

198
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:09,100
Someone who's eloquent uses big words, but is also very good at making other people listen.
能言善辩的人会用大词，但也非常擅长让别人倾听。

199
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:10,420
So it's usually about speaking.
所以这通常与说话有关。

200
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:12,660
So you would say he's an eloquent speaker.
所以你可以说他是一个能言善辩的演讲者。

201
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,660
That's right.
没错。

202
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:18,700
So someone who is eloquent is fun or good or interesting to listen to.
所以，一个口才好的人，听起来有趣、好听或引人入胜。

203
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:24,920
And our last description for personalities and the way people are is a person that's
我们最后一个描述性格和为人方式的词是

204
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,920
daring.
大胆的。

205
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,640
Well, this can be a good thing or a bad thing.
嗯，这可能是好事也可能是坏事。

206
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,360
