这取决于你在说谁。

207
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:36,400
Because sometimes daring people are also reckless and this can be dangerous.
因为有时候大胆的人也很鲁莽，这可能很危险。

208
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:39,520
But sometimes someone who is daring can be doing good things.
但有时候大胆的人也能做好事。

209
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:44,360
Like a daring business person might take risks that other people don't take.
比如一个大胆的商人可能会冒别人不敢冒的风险。

210
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,360
Okay.
好的。

211
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:49,480
So a person that's daring dares to take risks, right?
所以，一个大胆的人敢于冒险，对吧？

212
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,000
You are very daring.
你非常大胆。

213
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,960
You Marco are daring because recently you jumped out of an airplane.
你，Marco，很大胆，因为你最近从飞机上跳了下来。

214
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,960
Yeah.
是啊。

215
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,040
You did some skydiving.
你跳了伞。

216
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,540
So that would be considered daring.
所以那就算是大胆。

217
00:09:58,540 --> 00:09:59,540
That's very daring.
那非常大胆。

218
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:03,360
I'm not daring like that because I would never jump out of an airplane.
我可没那么大胆，因为我绝不会从飞机上跳下来。

219
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,360
Right.
对。

220
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,360
Okay.
好的。

221
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:09,040
So we took a look at basically 10 key words here.
所以我们基本上看了10个关键词。

222
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:13,400
A lot of adjectives, but they're a great way to describe yourself.
很多形容词，但它们是描述自己的好方法。

223
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:18,240
Maybe if you're at a job interview, sometimes a typical question is, how would you describe
也许在求职面试时，一个常见的问题是：你如何描述自己？

224
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,360
